author: @thomasblaze
text: Electron is basically just packaged NodeJS + Chrome to give it GUI capability via browser windows. It's a package manager like npm or yarn giving warnings about packages it's installing, likely from `npm audit` or a similar command/tool. Deprecation just means it's going to eventually be removed from the API so it's discouraged to use it going forward, so the devs should update their projects; as seen in Java, or even more often Android.  I'm guessing you already know most/all of this, but hopefully someone else doesn't.
